This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with automated polyp detection in colonoscopy videos using deep learning methods. It also involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Additionally, the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it involves the use of deep learning methods for automated polyp detection. Information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories may also be relevant as the paper deals with the analysis of colonoscopy videos for detecting polyps.
